{ __init__() }
- Initialization method that is a constructor
- two types of them
    --> Default, Parameterized

{Attr}
Object Attr:
    - self : used when different data for different objects eg, student name
Class Attr:
    - data which is common for all objs
exception case:
    - if both attributes have same name with different data then the obj attr has greater precedency than the calss attr


M E T H O D S:
---------------
Static Methods:
    - Which doesn't need the Self Parameter
    - as self is used for each objs
    - The methods which doesn't need objects, but direct working in the class level
